A4.text: Mustafa Abdul Jalil was the Chairman of the National Transitional Council from 5 March 2011 until its dissolution on 8 August 2012.

A5.text: This position meant he was de facto head of state during a transitional period after the fall of Muammar Gaddafi's government in the Libyan Civil War, and until the handover of power to the General National Congress.
